Happy Sunday everyone! Reflecting on where I am in life today: My life has taken me to some amazing places. Sitting here, last year, at the edge of Cliffs of Moher in Ireland, where Harry Potter was filmed. 

However, the greatest of all journeys I’ve been granted in my life is an inner journey. As a man in recovery, it took me a very long time to learn to love myself, and to appreciate the man that I am. Today, I get to experience life through the lens of gratitude and humility. 

Not everyone is meant to walk this path with us, which is why it is so important that I get to walk it with self-love, kindness, compassion and dignity. 

Whenever there is inner turmoil, it’s God’s way to refocus and redirect our thinking. It’s when it’s time to take action and move past the uncomfortable, through vulnerability and with honesty to self. 

The longest journey in life is not on a plane to visit beautiful countries. It is from the mind, to the heart, through the soul. Letting go is the single most rewarding experience in life. Yet, many times, the most painful. 

Sending positive energy and loving vibes to all who need it today! And trusting God’s plan. He ALWAYS has my back. Much love ❤️

Thank You 🙏 God for my life today! 

Soul searching. Discovering myself, traveling the world. 
One country, one day at a time. Here on the rooftop of the Axel Hotel in Madrid, Friday evening. What a wonderful journey. Finding oneself alone, in a distant new place creates an impactful shift of perspective. The world is a beautiful and vast place full of people of all nationalities, genders, races, colors, cultures. Yet, at the core of who we are, we are all the same. 

Embarking on a spiritual journey of growth and acceptance one truly discovers God’s greatest gifts to us: the gift of presence. All we have to do is show up, authentically, vulnerably and free from expectation. What we find is magic. We meet people, places, situations, moments that change us, grow us, and humbly allow us to see just how important we each are to the fabric of this beautiful life. I’m return we get to bring our light and our presence to make others feel seen, heard, valued and simply loved. 

Thank you to all you beautiful travelers I met along my way. I’m changed for the better for having met each of you. 🙌🏼🙏❤️

13 years ago today I walked into the rooms of AA and CMA; a broken, desperate, desolate, fearful and selfish man who had been brought to my knees by drugs and alcohol. I wanted to die. Remorsefully, I would beg God not let me wake up the morning following after another run — yet again, I succumbed to my addiction. Days turned to months, months turned to years. I lived to use, and used to live. 

God had a different plan for how  my life would unravel. Last time I used, I admitted to my innermost self that I was completely powerless and my life had become unmanageable. I finally became honest with myself and surrendered, and desperately needed help.

“When the student is ready, the teacher appears” is one of my favorite quotes, because it’s true, every time. When we’re ready to accept help, all necessary support appears. Mostly in the faces of fellows that had recovered themselves before me. Through the steps, they guided me on how to live life without having to use again. These men and women loved me until I learned to love myself. 

Today, as I celebrate 13 years of continuous sobriety, I thank each and every person that has shown me love, support and encouragement. The single most important priority in my life today is God, my sobriety, my program. Today, I get to live a life I never knew could be possible for someone like me. A life I no longer seek to sabotage. I stepped out of my own way and God has shown me a life beyond anything my mind could have envisioned. I have complete trust in my Higher Power guiding me.

Life isn’t meant to be perfect. It is meant to be lived. It has ups and downs, it brings love and pain; it brings laughter and tears; it brings success and failures; it boasts life, and sadly we grow through the pain of death. It is both beautiful and challenging. It’s in this balance that I get to live my life fully and purposefully. It is in this balance where I get to discover the magic of Self love. Self-worth. And most importantly selflessness.

Thank You 🙏 God for my life today, and thank you all for the love and support you’ve shown me through the years. Much love ❤️
